 SCIOPS 01.36: Rearview Mirror
===============================



  

 Hi friends. SCIOPS is going on hiatus for the holidays. I'll return to you in January with volume 02, all new and yet somehow improved. In the meantime, I have a gift for you.
   

  

 I programmed a little AI and trained it on all 35 issues of SCIOPS volume 01. It's not very smart, but then, neither am I. Tell me what you think -- have I automated myself out of a job?
   

  

 Enjoy this year-in-review, and I'll see you in 2018, the Year of Oh No What Next...
   

  

![](data:image/gif;base64,)
  

 A shorter one this week, as I've got a president, a billionaire and a demagogue completely hardwired to do my bidding. So on our planet, unlike all the other memes that host has acquired. This does away with some of the problematic memes I want to target.
   

  

 But that's not what I'm trying to get inside your skull.
   

  

 Instead, I want to talk about climate change and eco-catastrophe. Your money or your life. What if an AI were, right now, making subtle moves to take over the world, I need access to construction materials. The modern world is in a state of cognitive dissonance.
   

  

 Look at the following images. red and black horizontal gridgreen and black horizontal gridgreen and black horizontal grid Really look at them. Anything untrue isn't there to be interacted with.
   

  

 Boomers complain that no one person can solve.
   

  

 If the legitimacy of the nation-state is built on Ethereum, but specially designed to decentralize heavy computation. So the less art and craft your job requires, the sooner a job will be automated. We actually benefit from solitude at this time, they'll remember us for it.
   

  

 Yet it isn't fantasy -- it's a donation, not an investment.
   

  

 Maybe capitalism with AI is going to the development of internet technology. Send it to your kids!
   

  

 The better cognitive security we have, the more powerful and dangerous than earlier forms  thats certainly a possibility.
   

  

 Instead of the army with the biggest factories, the tee-shirted nerds with the biggest guns, or the capitalist with the biggest guns, or the capitalist with the biggest incentives. There are hordes of hackers constantly trying to get inside your skull.
   

  

 This week I'll share the key idea to making the next word match the previous ones.
   

  

 The memes have to get into your head,
   

 Max
